verses.text_plain: Keep thy foot when thou goest to the house of God, and be more ready to hear, than to give the sacrifice of fools: for they consider not that they do evil.
verses.verse_html: 1Keep thy foot when thou goest to the house of God, and be more ready to hear, than to give the sacrifice of fools: for they consider not that they do evil.

verses.text_plain: Be not rash with thy mouth, and let not thine heart be hasty to utter any thing before God: for God is in heaven, and thou upon earth: therefore let thy words be few.
verses.verse_html:
2Be not rash with thy mouth, and let not thine heart be hasty to utter any thing before God: for God is in heaven, and thou upon earth: therefore let thy words be few. ▼
▼ thing: or, word

verses.text_plain: For a dream cometh through the multitude of business; and a fool’s voice is known by multitude of words.
verses.verse_html: 3For a dream cometh through the multitude of business; and a fool’s voice is known by multitude of words.

verses.text_plain: When thou vowest a vow unto God, defer not to pay it; for he hath no pleasure in fools: pay that which thou hast vowed.
verses.verse_html: 4When thou vowest a vow unto God, defer not to pay it; for he hath no pleasure in fools: pay that which thou hast vowed.

verses.text_plain: Better is it that thou shouldest not vow, than that thou shouldest vow and not pay.
verses.verse_html: 5Better is it that thou shouldest not vow, than that thou shouldest vow and not pay.

verses.text_plain: Suffer not thy mouth to cause thy flesh to sin; neither say thou before the angel, that it was an error: wherefore should God be angry at thy voice, and destroy the work of thine hands?
verses.verse_html: 6Suffer not thy mouth to cause thy flesh to sin; neither say thou before the angel, that it was an error: wherefore should God be angry at thy voice, and destroy the work of thine hands?

verses.text_plain: For in the multitude of dreams and many words there are also divers vanities: but fear thou God.
verses.verse_html: 7For in the multitude of dreams and many words there are also divers vanities: but fear thou God.

verses.text_plain: If thou seest the oppression of the poor, and violent perverting of judgment and justice in a province, marvel not at the matter: for he that is higher than the highest regardeth; and there be higher than they.
verses.verse_html:
8If thou seest the oppression of the poor, and violent perverting of judgment and justice in a province, marvel not at the matter: for he that is higher than the highest regardeth; and there be higher than they. ▼
▼ at the…: Heb. at the will, or, purpose

footnotes.body_text: ▼ at the…: Heb. at the will, or, purpose
footnotes.body_html: ▼ at the…: Heb. at the will, or, purpose

verses.text_plain: Moreover the profit of the earth is for all: the king himself is served by the field.
verses.verse_html: 9Moreover the profit of the earth is for all: the king himself is served by the field.

verses.text_plain: He that loveth silver shall not be satisfied with silver; nor he that loveth abundance with increase: this is also vanity.
verses.verse_html: 10He that loveth silver shall not be satisfied with silver; nor he that loveth abundance with increase: this is also vanity.

verses.text_plain: When goods increase, they are increased that eat them: and what good is there to the owners thereof, saving the beholding of them with their eyes?
verses.verse_html: 11When goods increase, they are increased that eat them: and what good is there to the owners thereof, saving the beholding of them with their eyes?

verses.text_plain: The sleep of a labouring man is sweet, whether he eat little or much: but the abundance of the rich will not suffer him to sleep.
verses.verse_html: 12The sleep of a labouring man is sweet, whether he eat little or much: but the abundance of the rich will not suffer him to sleep.

verses.text_plain: There is a sore evil which I have seen under the sun, namely, riches kept for the owners thereof to their hurt.
verses.verse_html: 13There is a sore evil which I have seen under the sun, namely, riches kept for the owners thereof to their hurt.

verses.text_plain: But those riches perish by evil travail: and he begetteth a son, and there is nothing in his hand.
verses.verse_html: 14But those riches perish by evil travail: and he begetteth a son, and there is nothing in his hand.

verses.text_plain: As he came forth of his mother’s womb, naked shall he return to go as he came, and shall take nothing of his labour, which he may carry away in his hand.
verses.verse_html: 15As he came forth of his mother’s womb, naked shall he return to go as he came, and shall take nothing of his labour, which he may carry away in his hand.

verses.text_plain: And this also is a sore evil, that in all points as he came, so shall he go: and what profit hath he that hath laboured for the wind?
verses.verse_html: 16And this also is a sore evil, that in all points as he came, so shall he go: and what profit hath he that hath laboured for the wind?

verses.text_plain: All his days also he eateth in darkness, and he hath much sorrow and wrath with his sickness.
verses.verse_html: 17All his days also he eateth in darkness, and he hath much sorrow and wrath with his sickness.

verses.text_plain: Behold that which I have seen: it is good and comely for one to eat and to drink, and to enjoy the good of all his labour that he taketh under the sun all the days of his life, which God giveth him: for it is his portion.
verses.verse_html:
18Behold that which I have seen: it is good and comely for one to eat and to drink, and to enjoy the good of all his labour that he taketh under the sun all the days of his life, which God giveth him: for it is his portion. ▼
▼ it is good…: Heb. there is a good which is comely, etc
 , ▼
▼ all the days: Heb. the number of the days

footnotes.body_text: ▼ it is good…: Heb. there is a good which is comely, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ it is good…: Heb. there is a good which is comely, etc

footnotes.body_text: ▼ all the days: Heb. the number of the days
footnotes.body_html: ▼ all the days: Heb. the number of the days

verses.text_plain: Every man also to whom God hath given riches and wealth, and hath given him power to eat thereof, and to take his portion, and to rejoice in his labour; this is the gift of God.
verses.verse_html: 19Every man also to whom God hath given riches and wealth, and hath given him power to eat thereof, and to take his portion, and to rejoice in his labour; this is the gift of God.

verses.text_plain: For he shall not much remember the days of his life; because God answereth him in the joy of his heart.
verses.verse_html:
20For he shall not much remember the days of his life; because God answereth him in the joy of his heart. ▼
▼ For…: or, Though he give not much, yet he remembereth, etc
